  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration - Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nLegal definitions typically require:\n- Intentional concealment of illegal funds\n- Knowledge that money originated from criminal activity\n- Deliberate attempts to disguise the money's origin\n- Transactions designed to hide the source of funds\n\nSpecific details and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction. If you need precise legal information, I recommend consulting local legal resources or an attorney specializing in financial crimes.",
